  "design_notes": "The chart is designed for standard difficulty, capturing the laid-back synthwave tempo of 88 BPM. It starts sparse in the intro to allow the player to settle in, mapping melody-focused high band elements to a natural left-to-right sweep across the lanes. As the energy curve rises around bar 6, the density of notes naturally scales, transitioning into syncopated, sync-happy mid-tempo taps. Hold placements are selected deliberately from valid sustain candidates (exactly 4 holds across 33 events, making up 12% of the chart) to mirror prolonged synthesizer chords. Each hold has a clear 1-beat spacing afterward to guarantee clean lane recovery and standard-difficulty flow, fully respecting the 0.5-beat division budget.",
